21
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:38,640
They're all pouring into Blue Ocean.

22
00:02:40,270 --> 00:02:40,800
We've had investors

23
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,590
pull out?

24
00:02:44,750 --> 00:02:46,240
But I hear Blue Ocean

25
00:02:46,830 --> 00:02:48,830
is backed by Yaohui Co.

26
00:02:53,590 --> 00:02:55,590
Blue Ocean excels in operations,

27
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,870
while we've been strong in content.

28
00:02:58,520 --> 00:03:00,030
Anyway, it's not the end of the world.

29
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:02,030
We'll push forward and compete.

30
00:03:02,990 --> 00:03:03,870
Head-to-head.

31
00:03:04,710 --> 00:03:05,430
I'm afraid I have no strength now.

32
00:03:07,550 --> 00:03:08,550
How?

33
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:11,480
We've been working together for so long.

34
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:15,360
I'll tell you the truth.

35
00:03:15,710 --> 00:03:16,960
I've been thinking

36
00:03:18,870 --> 00:03:19,960
about quitting.

37
00:03:21,480 --> 00:03:22,270
Quitting?

38
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:25,150
But why?

39
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:26,680
No particular reason.

40
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:29,360
It's the board's decision.

41
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,550
They want to sell the company.

42
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:34,080
But you're the founder.

43
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:35,830
How can they ask you to leave?

44
00:03:36,990 --> 00:03:38,990
They want to sell off the company?

45
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:42,870
Being a founder

46
00:03:43,030 --> 00:03:44,200
doesn't mean much here.

47
00:03:44,590 --> 00:03:46,920
It's all about what the capital wants.

48
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,520
If they want to sell, then they sell.

49
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:49,150
Who are we to say no?

50
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,550
But it might not be so bad.

51
00:03:52,590 --> 00:03:53,240
See,

52
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:54,480
